      • fire

        void fire(String type,
          com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject detail,
          com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject options)
        Fires a custom event. The options object can contain the following properties: node: Node to fire the event on (defaults to this). bubbles: Whether the event should bubble. Defaults to true. cancelable: Whether the event can be canceled with preventDefault. Defaults to false.

      • async

        Object async(Function method,
             int wait)
        Calls method asynchronously. If no wait time is specified, runs tasks with microtask timing (after the current method finishes, but before the next event from the event queue is processed). Returns a handle that can be used to cancel the task.

      • cancelAsync

        void cancelAsync(Object handle)
        Cancels the identified async task.

      • transform

        void transform(String transform,
               com.google.gwt.dom.client.Element node)
        Applies a CSS transform to the specified node, or host element if no node is specified. transform is specified as a string. For example: transform('rotateX(90deg)', elm);

      • translate3d

        void translate3d(String x,
                 String y,
                 String z,
                 com.google.gwt.dom.client.Element node)
        Transforms the specified node, or host element if no node is specified. For example: translate3d('100px', '100px', '100px', elm);

      • resolveUrl

        String resolveUrl(String url)
        Takes a URL relative to the of an imported Polymer element, and returns a path relative to the current document. This method can be used, for example, to refer to an asset delivered alongside an HTML import.
